-- Swatch Mulls Switch to Swiss Accounting Standard, F&W Reports
-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 2012-09-19T07:48:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-19/swatch-mulls-switch-to-swiss-accounting-standard-f-w-reports.html
Swatch Group AG (UHR)  is considering a
switch to Swiss GAAP FER accounting standards from IFRS, Finanz
& Wirtschaft reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Nick
Hayek.  “Over-regulation” under the IFRS standard is becoming a
“catastrophe,” Hayek said in an interview in today’s
 newspaper .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
 ddoherty9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 